### **1. System Installation and Base:**
- **Arch Linux**: Base installation
- **Base-devel**: Development tools (compilers, libraries, etc.)
- **NetworkManager**: For managing network connections

### **2. Display Server and Window Manager:**
- **Hyprland**: Wayland compositor
- **swaybg**: Background image manager for Wayland
- **alacritty**: Terminal emulator
- **wlroots**: Required by Hyprland for Wayland compatibility

### **3. AMD Graphics Drivers for Wayland:**
- **mesa**: OpenGL/Vulkan drivers for AMD
- **vulkan-radeon**: Vulkan driver for AMD GPUs
- **libva-mesa-driver**: VA-API support (video acceleration)
- **mesa-vdpau**: VDPAU support (video decoding)

### **4. GUI Elements:**
- **Waybar**: Status bar for Wayland
- **Rofi**: Application launcher
- **xdg-desktop-portal**: For Flatpak or Snap integration and application permissions
- **swaylock**: Lock screen (if needed for Hyprland)

### **5. Terminal and Terminal-based Utilities:**
- **tmux**: Terminal multiplexer
- **ranger**: Terminal file manager
- **neovim**: Text editor
- **nano**: Text editor
- **btop**: System monitoring tool
- **zsh**: Shell (instead of bash)
- **oh-my-zsh** or **zsh-syntax-highlighting**: Useful zsh plugins
- **git**: Version control

### **6. Development Tools:**
- **gcc** and **clang**: C/C++ compilers
- **cmake**: Build system generator
- **python**: Scripting and programming language
- **nodejs** and **npm**: JavaScript runtime and package manager

### **7. Audio:**
- **pipewire**: Modern audio system (replaces PulseAudio)
- **pipewire-pulse**: PulseAudio compatibility layer for PipeWire
- **wireplumber**: PipeWire session manager
- **pavucontrol**: GUI for audio control
- **pamixer**: Terminal-based audio control
- **alsa-utils**: Low-level audio control and troubleshooting tools

### **8. Bluetooth:**
- **bluez**: Bluetooth protocol stack
- **bluez-utils**: Additional Bluetooth tools
- **blueman**: Bluetooth manager with GUI
- **pipewire-bluetooth**: For Bluetooth audio device support

### **9. Clipboard Management:**
- **wl-clipboard**: Clipboard utilities for Wayland
- **clipman**: Clipboard manager for Wayland

### **10. Gaming:**
- **steam**: Gaming platform
- **lutris**: Game management platform
- **proton**: Compatibility layer for running Windows games

### **11. Multimedia:**
- **mpv**: Video player
- **vlc**: Optional media player
- **imagemagick**: For image manipulation

### **12. File Management:**
- **ranger**: Terminal-based file manager
- **syncthing**: File synchronization

### **13. Power Management:**
- **tlp**: Power management optimization
- **upower**: Power status and battery management
- **acpid**: Power and event handling

### **14. Fonts and Themes:**
- **nerd-fonts**: For enhanced terminal font support
- **arc-theme** or **adapta-gtk-theme**: GTK themes (if using GTK applications)
- **papirus-icon-theme**: Optional icon theme

### **15. Notification Management:**
- **mako**: Lightweight notification daemon for Wayland

### **16. Screenshot and Screen Recording:**
- **grim**: Screenshot tool for Wayland
- **slurp**: Region selection for screenshots
- **swappy**: Screenshot editor for Wayland
- **wf-recorder**: Screen recorder for Wayland

### **17. Security:**
- **ufw**: Uncomplicated Firewall
- **fail2ban**: Protection from brute force attacks

### **18. Backup and Sync:**
- **rsync**: File synchronization and backup
- **timeshift**: System restore utility

### **19. AUR Package Management:**
- **yay**: AUR helper for installing AUR packages

---

### **Fun and Aesthetic Tools:**
- **neofetch**: System information tool for showing off your system setup
- **16-color pywal**: Generates color schemes based on images and applies them to your terminal and apps

---

### **Essential GUI Applications:**
- **firefox**: Web browser
- **discord**: Voice and text chat platform
- **telegram-desktop**: Telegram messaging app
- **thunderbird**: Email client (can replace with **mutt** or **aerc** for terminal-based clients)
- **yacreader**: Comic book reader
